Recently was introduced to a fun activity called geocaching.  OMG, so much fun.  You use a GPS system to hunt for coordinates that are posted on the website.  When you find the object which is usually a film canister or a box of some sort your write your name on the log and then post on the site.  This is an extremely basic description.  But look it up it's like a world wide scavenger hunt.  ^_^

http://www.geocaching.com/

I don't post often but i decided to take some time and inform people of whats going on in my life.  Culinary school is great, having the time of my life.  I took Latin cuisine and baking this quarter and I'm pretty sure I earned an A in both classes.  My Chef for latin is chef Castro.  He's a very interesting little puerto rican man.  Always very nice and helpful, we're always taking about the italian and puerto rican influences in NY.  The other day I told him there was nothing wrong with brooklyn and he said nothing but the people.  Ouch low blow to all the brooklynights out there.  

My baking chef reminds me a lot of my family since she is a short italian woman.  Everyone finds her a little odd, because she randomly makes funny voices and sings in the middle of class.  She's also a big fan of playful banter, so a lot of people get offended.  I guess she doesn't bother me because I'm used to it.  

Other  than that I am applying for the Culinary institute of America in Hyde Park NY.  Yes, I know this will be my fourth college.  Don't think I haven't noticed.  However, I've finally found a career that really fits me and this school is the Harvard of Culinary schools.   I also want to transfer because I need a school that is strictly culinary.  Due to the fact that Ai s an art school it has to cater to many different art related degrees, which means my classes aren't always offered.  I really like the school, but I want culinary to be the only degrees available.  Call me selfish.  I think I'll be moving back to NY in a couple months.  Tell u more later.

So, I woke up this morning to my father dry heaving in the bathroom.  At first I thought he was brushing his teeth, because he was taught o brush the back of his freking throat.  Well the noise doesn't stop and finally I hear "I killed it" and "Omg he's dead."  Here I'm thinking my dog is dead, so I jump out of bed and ask what happened.  Well, it would seem that my brother's pet hamster, Chili, was dead.  Not only that but my dad stepped on him at 6 am.   He is bitching and moaning about how his entire day was ruined and he felt it squish under his foot.  None of us would go in the room and get it.  We had to call our hillbilly friend to clean it up.  On closer inspection we see that it was still whole and a bit slimy.  So we figure that one of the dogs killed, poor thing escapes it's tank and finds a dog.  My cockapoo, scooby, prances his way into the kitchen looking for love and praise.  I geuss we know who did it.  And that was my morning, joy rapture.

Stupid little men with daggers.  Anyway, I'm pretty sure I got the job at the tampa bay preforming arts center.  Oce the background check clears it will be official.  The only downside is that I might have to drop hallo scream, but they understand.              

 on another note this is my kitten and my bunny.  Loki is the rabbit and Hermes is my kitten.   Despite what you might think they actually do play together, when it's not two in the morning like it was when I took the pictures. ^_^

Alright people, I've thought long and hard about my future.  I've decided to apply to the art institute of tampa as a culinary managment major.  I'm doing fine at USF and I like the campus, but I feel like I'm on a fast track to nowhere.  I don't want to be stuck in an office all my life.  I want to create and the only thing I can create that will also support me is food.  So thats it, I haven't felt this sure of anything for a while.  Thats how I know I'm going in the right direction.  Wish me luck.

Hey guys I was wondering if anyone would like a cat or knows of somone who might want one.  My room mate and I found a female cat outside in a thunderstorm about two months ago.  She was filthy and half starving.  We took her in fed and cleaned her.  We believe that she was abandoned because she was already litter trained when we found her.  She is extremely affectionate and friendly.  Unfortunatly we do not have the time or funds to keep her.  Not to mention that we are not allowed to have pets and I'm allergic to cats. Her name is misty.  please tell me if you know of anyone who would like to give this beautiful cat a home. We will also give them the litter box and everything else we have that belongs to misty.

I went on a bit of a movie spree this week and went to see "V for Vendetta" and "The Hills Have Eyes."

    Now let me just say that I did not finish "The Hills"  I walked out after and hour and fifteen minutes.  This is due to the fact that they were raping one of the girls.  It was a disgusting scene.  The two men were laughing and raping this girl and then they started petting the infant.  It was not horror it was disgusting.  There was no reason for them to rape her.  And it's not like the scene was short.  oh no, they just kept going for few minutes all there was, was rape.  I could have dealt with them simply beating her to death and ripping her to pieces.  It was a total violation of the senses.  Not only could you see her struggle try to protect her body with blamkets but you could hear it.  Every painful noise she mad in time with the abuse.  Sorry, I had to leave.


     On a more positive note I really enjoyed "V."  It was like "the phantom of the opera" mixed with "1984."  Really good.  Definatly something worth seeing.
